1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Just thinking about that song as I was standing back there

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:06,000
and thinking about the words to that song

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:10,000
and David making this statement in Psalm 34.

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Notice in the first couple of verses,

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:16,000
I will bless the Lord at all times.

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
His praise shall continually be in my mouth.

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:22,000
My soul shall make her boast in the Lord.

8
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:25,000
The humble shall hear thereof and be glad.

9
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Oh, magnify the Lord with me

10
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,000
and let us exalt his name together.

11
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,000
And there were times during the life

12
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:35,000
and ministry of the Lord Jesus Christ

13
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,000
where some were worshiping

14
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
and others tried to prevent them from worshiping.

15
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
And Jesus said, let her alone. Amen.

16
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Why? She'd been saved. She'd been forgiven.

17
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,000
And what a blessing.

18
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,000
I think about the Lord when he's that triumphal entry

19
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,000
and the disciples and all those are gathered

20
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,000
and they're worshiping.

21
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
And he says, if they hold their peace,

22
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,000
the rocks will cry out. Amen.

23
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:58,000
And don't make the rocks do the job

24
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,000
that we were designed to do.

25
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:03,000
And that is to praise and worship the Lord.

26
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:05,000
And what a blessing.

27
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Thank the Lord for that.

28
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Second Corinthians chapter number seven.

29
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Second Corinthians chapter number seven.

30
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
And be looking at verses two through 16 this morning

31
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,000
as we finish this passage of scripture.

32
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
We entered into the first verse last Sunday morning

33
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:20,000
as we really focused at the end of chapter six

34
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,000
and entered into the first verse of chapter seven

35
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,000
and looked at that truth of biblical separation.

36
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,000
And what a blessing to understand

37
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,000
that God has a plan for our lives.

38
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,000
As we enter here into the seventh chapter

39
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:35,000
and verse two through the end of the chapter,

40
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:39,000
we find that the Apostle Paul picks up here

41
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
where he left off in chapter two.

42
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:44,000
And you say, well, that's a big gap.

43
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
There's a big parenthetical in the book of Second Corinthians

44
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:50,000
where he begins to talk about the ministry

45
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,000
at the end of chapter two

46
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
and then chapter three, four, five,

47
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:58,000
and much of chapter six is dealing with the ministry.

48
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,000
And we find that the Apostle Paul,

49
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
if you want to think about the particular text

50
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,000
in chapter one and verse number 12

51
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
all the way through chapter two and verse number 13,

52
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
the Apostle Paul addressed the matter

53
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,000
that here he will now resume speaking about.

54
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:16,000
We understand as we mentioned

55
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
by way of introduction last week

56
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:20,000
that the Apostle Paul cared deeply

57
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,000
about the believers in Corinth.

58
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
He had mentioned to them in verse 11 of chapter six

59
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,000
how his mouth was open unto them,

60
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,000
how his heart was enlarged,

61
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,000
and he desired to be able to impart

62
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,000
some spiritual truth to them.

63
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
He understood that God had given him a message

64
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,000
to deliver to the people at the church in Corinth,

65
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,000
but they had angst in their heart against him,

66
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,000
some within the church.

67
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,000
And because of this difficulty and this misunderstanding,

68
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:52,000
there were some that would not receive the message

69
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:55,000
that the Apostle Paul was commanded to preach.

70
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,000
As we enter into this passage of scripture,

71
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,000
I've titled the message

72
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:03,000
Restoring Strained Relationships.

73
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,000
And you saw that on the back of the bulletin this morning,

74
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
restoring strained relationships.

75
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:12,000
God has created us as human beings,

76
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,000
as relational beings.

77
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,000
We are relational.

78
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,000
As you live life,

79
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
you learn that relationships can be strained

80
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:22,000
from time to time.

81
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:26,000
We find that the cause of that particular strain

82
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,000
in that particular relationship,

83
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,000
the causes are varied and plenteous.

84
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:33,000
There are many times that we understand

85
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,000
you live life for any period of time,

86
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,000
there's a number of things

87
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:40,000
that can cause a relationship to be strained.

88
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:44,000
The cause of that strain

89
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
sometimes is easy to identify.

90
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:50,000
It's easy for us to know what strained this relationship.

91
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,000
Often, however, a relationship is strained

92
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,000
and then that's followed by pride,

93
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:59,000
anger, and bitterness.

94
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:00,000
And then what happens?

95
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Well, that relationship continues to further deteriorate.

96
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:08,000
It's now not just strained, maybe fractured.

97
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:11,000
We can see the progression of this.

98
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
We find that the Apostle Paul loved the people in Corinth

99
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,000
and throughout the text of Scripture here

100
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:17,000
that we'll look at this morning,

101
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
we find that his desire is to see

102
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,000
that strained relationship restored.

103
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,000
I believe that it's extremely obvious

104
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,000
as you look throughout the text.

105
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,000
The Bible deals with many subjects.

106
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,000
I'm thankful for the Bible.

107
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,000
The B-I-B-L-E, yes, that's the book for me, amen?

108
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,000
We say that it's the sole authority

109
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:36,000
for faith and practice.

110
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
That's what we would say as Baptist people,

111
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,000
that the Bible is the sole authority

112
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,000
for faith and for practice.

113
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,000
There are portions of Scripture

114
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,000
that are extremely doctrinal in nature.

115
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,000
We can look at those portions of Scripture

116
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:52,000
and we can find the doctrinal truth that is given

117
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,000
and we talk about for faith, that's the doctrine

118
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:57,000
and doctrine matters.

119
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Doctrine is important.

120
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,000
We find that the Bible says

121
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:05,000
that all Scripture is given by inspiration of God.

122
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,000
It's profitable for doctrine.

123
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:10,000
We understand the importance of sound doctrine

124
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:12,000
and repeated throughout the Scriptures,

125
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:15,000
but we find that we come to other portions of Scripture

126
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:18,000
and they're extremely practical.

127
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:21,000
Now, all of God's Word is to be applied in our lives.

128
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:23,000
We're to be doers of the Word,

129
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,000
but I believe this morning

130
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,000
and I am convinced today that the Lord

131
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:31,000
has preserved this portion of Scripture for us

132
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,000
because each of us will experience

133
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,000
strained relationships in life.

134
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,000
And this passage of Scripture

135
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,000
is extremely practical in nature.

136
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,000
The passage of Scripture that is before us

137
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:43,000
is designed that God gave it to us.

138
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,000
It's profitable for us.

139
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,000
It's to help us.

140
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:49,000
And as we look at this passage of Scripture

141
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,000
and as we consider the subject matter

142
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:54,000
of restoring strained relationships,

143
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,000
I believe that if we would be honest with ourselves,

144
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,000
if we'd be honest with the Lord,

145
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:02,000
that there may be one or many this morning

146
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,000
that if we would be honest,

147
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,000
we'd say we have some strained relationships.

148
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,000
The question is this.

149
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,000
What will you do about it?

150
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,000
Have you just gotten used to the strained relationship?

151
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,000
It is what it is.

152
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:14,000
You hear that term.

153
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Sometimes that term really bothers me.

154
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,000
It's so commonplace in our society today.

155
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Something happens, whatever,

156
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,000
and it's like it is what it is.

157
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,000
We hear it so often.

158
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,000
But with strained relationships, what will you do?

159
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,000
How will you respond?

160
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Do you desire for the relationship to be restored?

161
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:39,000
Will you humble yourself and trust the Lord

162
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:44,000
to restore the relationship that is strained?

163
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:46,000
Sometimes we just get used to living

164
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:48,000
the way that we're living.

165
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:49,000
You say, you know what?

166
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,000
It is what it is.

167
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,000
It's been this way.

168
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,000
It's beyond.

169
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,000
I don't even care anymore.

170
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Can I tell you this morning,

171
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,000
that's not a biblical attitude.

172
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
That's not a biblical approach to relationships.

173
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,000
As we look at the text,

174
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,000
begin reading with me in verse number two.

175
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,000
Notice the plea, receive us.

176
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,000
We have wronged no man.

177
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,000
We have corrupted no man.

178
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,000
We have defrauded no man.

179
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,000
I speak not this to condemn you.

180
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,000
For I have said before that you are in our hearts

181
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,000
to die and live with you.

182
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,000
Great is my boldness of speech toward you.

183
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Great is my glorying of you.

184
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,000
Notice he says, I am filled with comfort.

185
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:33,000
I am exceeding joyful in all our tribulation.

186
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,000
For when we were come into Macedonia,

187
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,000
our flesh had no rest,

188
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,000
but we were troubled on every side.

189
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,000
Without were fightings.

190
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,000
Within were fears.

191
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:43,000
Nevertheless, God that comforteth those

192
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,000
that are cast down,

193
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:49,000
comforted us by the coming of Titus.

194
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,000
Again, this is picking up from where we were

195
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:52,000
in the end of chapter one,

196
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:54,000
the beginning of chapter two.

197
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,000
Notice in verse number seven,

198
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:58,000
notice where he says, and not by his coming only.

199
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:01,000
So God used Titus to encourage,

200
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:04,000
to comfort Paul during this time of tribulation.

201
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,000
But he says not by his coming only,

202
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,000
but by the consolation.

203
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:12,000
Notice wherewith he was comforted in you.

204
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:15,000
So he's talking about the people in Corinth

205
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:17,000
and their relationship with Titus

206
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:20,000
and how Paul is saying yes by his coming,

207
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,000
but also by the comfort or the encouragement,

208
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,000
the consolation,

209
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,000
wherewith he was comforted in you

210
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:30,000
when he told us your earnest desire,

211
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,000
your mourning,

212
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:35,000
your fervent mind toward me

213
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,000
so that I rejoice the more.

214
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,000
Notice what Paul's desiring,

215
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,000
that the strained relationship would be restored

216
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:45,000
and he's dealing with what he's dealing with

217
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,000
in chapter one when you're misunderstood.

218
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:48,000
What do you do?

219
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,000
I preached that message at the beginning of the year.

220
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,000
How do we deal with misunderstandings?

221
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:56,000
The reality is that you have misunderstood somebody

222
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,000
at some point in your life

223
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:00,000
and you have been misunderstood by somebody

224
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,000
at some point in your life.

225
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:02,000
And so what do we do?

226
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,000
Well, I gave you two points in that message many months ago.

227
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,000
Number one, you must first examine yourself

228
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,000
and then after you've examined yourself,

229
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:14,000
then and only then can you explain yourself.

230
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:17,000
Oftentimes what happens is we try to explain ourselves

231
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,000
before we first examine ourselves

232
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:22,000
and we might come at it with pride and arrogance

233
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,000
and what have you,

234
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,000
but Paul first examined himself

235
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,000
and then he seeks to explain himself

236
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,000
and we find that now Paul is hearing

237
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:32,000
about those in Corinth.

238
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Again, it's not the entirety of the church in Corinth

239
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:36,000
that is opposed to Paul,

240
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,000
but there's a group of people

241
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:41,000
and he's talking about this relationship with Titus

242
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:45,000
and how Titus brought not only how he had been encouraged

243
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:49,000
but how he told Paul about their earnest desire.

244
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Notice where he says toward me.

245
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Notice in verse eight,

246
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,000
for though I made you sorry with a letter,

247
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,000
I do not repent,

248
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,000
though I did repent,

249
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,000
for I perceive that the same epistle

250
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,000
hath made you sorry,

251
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,000
though it were,

252
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,000
but I do not repent.

253
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,639
but for a season, what is he talking about

254
00:10:01,639 --> 00:10:02,480
in verse number 80?

255
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:04,199
He's talking about the first letter that he sent,

256
00:10:04,199 --> 00:10:05,840
the book of 1 Corinthians.

257
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,239
And in the book of 1 Corinthians,

258
00:10:07,239 --> 00:10:09,720
there were some hard things that Paul had to say.

259
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:12,640
It's under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God.

260
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:15,800
And Paul says, have you ever had to tell somebody truth

261
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:16,920
and you've kind of like,

262
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:19,200
I don't know how it's gonna be received.

263
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,700
And you know you have to give it,

264
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:22,280
but then you kind of regret giving it

265
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:23,280
because you don't know.

266
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:24,760
That's what Paul's saying here.

267
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:29,000
He's saying that he was giving this truth.

268
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:31,440
He says, it made you sorry.

269
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:34,479
And he says, I do not repent, though I did repent.

270
00:10:34,479 --> 00:10:35,599
And what's he talking about?

271
00:10:35,599 --> 00:10:38,380
It's not this wishy-washy kind of a situation,

272
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:40,919
but the reality is if you are ever in a position

273
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:43,119
where you have to deliver truth to someone,

274
00:10:43,119 --> 00:10:45,639
and I'm talking about truth that's difficult,

275
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:48,159
truth that maybe the hearer

276
00:10:48,159 --> 00:10:51,159
doesn't necessarily wanna hear, receive,

277
00:10:51,159 --> 00:10:54,400
it can cause you to have some internal conflict

278
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:57,799
where to speak the truth in love,

279
00:10:57,799 --> 00:10:59,439
according to the book of Ephesians.

280
00:10:59,439 --> 00:11:02,119
And so Paul, he's already told them how he loves them.

281
00:11:02,119 --> 00:11:04,959
He's already told them how his heart is enlarged.

282
00:11:04,959 --> 00:11:08,199
He's already told them how they're in his heart

283
00:11:08,199 --> 00:11:10,599
to die and live with you in verse number three.

284
00:11:10,599 --> 00:11:13,000
And so we find that now Paul's mentioning

285
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:16,680
about the impact that that first letter had.

286
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:21,959
Verse nine, now I rejoice.

287
00:11:21,959 --> 00:11:24,459
Not that you were made sorry, but notice when he says,

288
00:11:24,459 --> 00:11:27,940
but that you sorrowed to repentance.

289
00:11:27,940 --> 00:11:29,860
That means that there were,

290
00:11:29,860 --> 00:11:31,379
as we looked at chapter number two,

291
00:11:31,379 --> 00:11:33,900
there was some response to the message

292
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:36,980
that was delivered in the book of 1 Corinthians.

293
00:11:36,980 --> 00:11:39,819
And he says that he's rejoicing,

294
00:11:39,819 --> 00:11:41,819
not simply because they were sorry,

295
00:11:41,819 --> 00:11:45,099
but he's rejoicing because that sorrow

296
00:11:45,099 --> 00:11:47,900
worked towards repentance.

297
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:50,440
What a blessing to consider the perspective

298
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:52,459
of the apostle Paul as he looks here.

299
00:11:52,459 --> 00:11:53,800
Have you ever been in a situation

300
00:11:54,199 --> 00:11:55,319
where somebody's done something,

301
00:11:55,319 --> 00:11:56,440
maybe it's with your children,

302
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:59,720
but it's certainly not isolated to just children.

303
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:01,239
The fact of the matter is that all people

304
00:12:01,239 --> 00:12:05,000
could be in this category where someone gets caught

305
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,879
and then they say they're sorry.

306
00:12:06,879 --> 00:12:08,320
And maybe you've asked this question,

307
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,979
are you sorry because you got caught

308
00:12:10,979 --> 00:12:13,059
or are you sorry because of what you did?

309
00:12:13,059 --> 00:12:15,520
And you know that it's wrong before God.

310
00:12:15,520 --> 00:12:18,320
There's a great difference, amen?

311
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,600
And Paul is saying that the letter,

312
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,419
listen, God's word is profitable.

313
00:12:22,419 --> 00:12:24,020
There's some things in the word of God

314
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:25,860
that are gonna smack you in the face.

315
00:12:25,860 --> 00:12:27,139
There's some things in God's word

316
00:12:27,139 --> 00:12:30,220
that are gonna change how you're living right now,

317
00:12:30,220 --> 00:12:31,179
the things that you're doing.

318
00:12:31,179 --> 00:12:33,500
The truth is that we're to be conformed

319
00:12:33,500 --> 00:12:35,479
to the image of Christ, to his dear son

320
00:12:35,479 --> 00:12:36,860
is what the Bible tells us.

321
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:39,539
And we're to be like him and we're to be holy

322
00:12:39,539 --> 00:12:41,500
in all manner of conversation.

323
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,259
And sometimes we come to God's word,

324
00:12:43,259 --> 00:12:45,580
listen, don't get mad at the author,

325
00:12:45,580 --> 00:12:49,979
don't get mad at the preacher, just apply it in your life.

326
00:12:49,979 --> 00:12:52,600
And Paul says, I'm rejoicing

327
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:56,179
because the sorrow work towards repentance

328
00:12:56,179 --> 00:12:59,139
for you were made sorry after a godly manner

329
00:12:59,139 --> 00:13:02,380
that you might receive damage by us and nothing.

330
00:13:02,380 --> 00:13:05,380
Verse 10, for godly sorrow worketh repentance

331
00:13:05,380 --> 00:13:07,399
to salvation not to be repented of,

332
00:13:07,399 --> 00:13:09,779
but the sorrow of the world worketh death.

333
00:13:09,779 --> 00:13:12,380
Listen, what a joy to understand that.

334
00:13:12,380 --> 00:13:16,580
And we can talk about this in two senses this morning.

335
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:18,279
When you think about salvation,

336
00:13:18,279 --> 00:13:20,240
you repent and you believe.

337
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:22,559
It's not the idea of lordship salvation

338
00:13:22,559 --> 00:13:24,979
that you repent of every single sin you ever committed

339
00:13:24,979 --> 00:13:26,360
because you don't know what they are,

340
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,600
I don't know what they are,

341
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:30,000
but we turn from our own way,

342
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,399
we turn from our own thinking,

343
00:13:31,399 --> 00:13:34,179
we have a change of heart, a change of mind,

344
00:13:34,179 --> 00:13:37,000
a change in direction and we trust Jesus Christ

345
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:39,919
as our personal savior, repent and believe.

346
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:43,199
And then we find that as the people of God,

347
00:13:43,199 --> 00:13:46,880
that as we walk with God, as we sin,

348
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:50,679
we're to confess our sins, we're to repent of that.

349
00:13:50,679 --> 00:13:51,520
Why?

350
00:13:51,520 --> 00:13:53,399
So that we can have that sweet communion

351
00:13:53,399 --> 00:13:55,199
and fellowship with God.

352
00:13:55,199 --> 00:13:58,160
You know what repentance works for us as the people of God?

353
00:13:58,160 --> 00:14:02,039
He says that godly sorrow worketh repentance

354
00:14:02,039 --> 00:14:04,000
to salvation not to be repented of.

355
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:06,600
In other words, it brings joy.

356
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:07,440
Why?

357
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:10,240
Because my fellowship with my God is restored

358
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:12,460
and it's what it's designed to be.

359
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:16,519
But notice he says the sorrow of the world worketh death.

360
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:20,839
You know, people that don't have any hope,

361
00:14:20,839 --> 00:14:22,640
they don't know that God loves them.

362
00:14:23,679 --> 00:14:26,079
They don't know that God forgives,

363
00:14:26,079 --> 00:14:28,359
but they know that they're wicked.

364
00:14:28,359 --> 00:14:32,279
They know they've done some really terrible things.

365
00:14:32,279 --> 00:14:34,320
It worketh death

366
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:36,959
because they have nowhere to turn for forgiveness.

367
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:39,600
They don't know that with thee, with the Lord,

368
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,720
there is forgiveness.

369
00:14:40,720 --> 00:14:43,200
Verse 11, for behold this self same thing

370
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:45,119
that you sorrowed after a godly sort

371
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,279
with carefulness it wrought in you,

372
00:14:47,279 --> 00:14:48,920
yea, what clearing of yourselves,

373
00:14:48,920 --> 00:14:50,959
yea, what indignation, yea, what fear,

374
00:14:50,959 --> 00:14:52,359
yea, what vehement desire,

375
00:14:52,359 --> 00:14:54,679
yea, what zeal, yea, what revenge,

376
00:14:54,679 --> 00:14:56,679
in all things you have approved yourselves

377
00:14:56,679 --> 00:14:59,799
to be clear in this matter.

378
00:14:59,799 --> 00:15:01,880
Wherefore, though I wrote unto you,

379
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:05,000
I did it not for this cause that had,

380
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:07,600
for his cause, excuse me, that had done the wrong,

381
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,839
nor for his cause that suffered wrong.

382
00:15:09,839 --> 00:15:11,640
Notice what he says at the end of verse 12,

383
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:15,079
but for our care for you in the sight of God

384
00:15:15,079 --> 00:15:17,480
